            <div class=""sub_stand_out"">
                <h3 class=""small_heading""> II. 1. Program origin </h3>
                <p class=""description""> 
                    International relations occupy an important place in historiography and research. International relations are the analysis and explanation of the
                    relations established between states through politicians (diplomatic acts) but also the relationships established by individuals with other
                    individuals across borders. These two relations are inseparable from each other, even if one of them can be predominant. International relations
                    therefore study the actions of politicians, economic actors an");
            WriteLiteral(@"d non-political actor interactions that cross borders. These relationships can be
                    economic, social, legal, etc. In doing so, any country that wants to find a place in the concert of nations is called to build excellent diplomatic
